cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper discusses security and privacy issues in wireless mesh networks, which are a type of wireless network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper specifically focuses on security threats and defense mechanisms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses trust management approaches, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
